\par\pard\plain \tx0\ltrch\loch {\f4\fs22\b1\i0\cf5 <$Scr_Ps::2>Leading Context:<!$Scr_Ps::2><$Scr_Ps::3>}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\li360\fi360\sa120\ltrch\loch {\f3\fs22\b0\i0\cf6 In the previous scene, Evan went to check out the phone festival, leaving Laura and Maggie time to finish the dinner and search Evan's company website to find out more about him. While Maggie still is both apprehensive and resistant to going to the fall festival with Evan, Laura wears her down and Maggie agrees to accompany Evan at the fall festival. This scene picks up where Evan returns to pick up Maggie and they head to Naperville's Riverwalk to get to know each other before the phone festival. Evan was able to eliminate whatever apprehension and resistance Maggie still have left, and she agreed bypass the dating phase and begin a relationship with him. The mood swings from high to low at the end of the scene, when Maggie innocently asks about Evan's ex-wife, Sarah, providing a downturn of Evan's emotions at the end of the scene.<!$Scr_Ps::3><$Scr_Ps::2>}
