\par\pard\plain \tx0\ltrch\loch {\f4\fs22\b1\i0\cf5 Character Emotional State:<!$Scr_Ps::2><$Scr_Ps::3>}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\li346\fi14\sb60\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f4\fs22\b1\i0\cf7 - Evan:}{\f3\fs22\b0\i0\cf1 <$Scr_Cs::5> Evan begins the scene quite nervous. He's worried that he came off as a fool and that Maggie would not be at the restaurant when he returned. His enthusiasm skyrocketed when he saw that Maggie and Laura had waited for him. While he would've been happy to have Laura join them, he was glad that Laura left them alone to get to know each other. The bulk of the scene is Evan going into problem-solving mode, with a touch of light humor along the way, knocking down Maggie's objections and concerns one by one until finally she relents and agrees to start a relationship with him. At that point, Evan is extremely excited. However as the scene ends, Maggie innocently asks about Sarah, bringing Evan's energy way down. The scene ends with Evan uncharacteristically  opening up to Maggie and admitting his pain. He is comforted by her hug to end the scene.<!$Scr_Cs::5>}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\li360\fi360\sa120\ltrch\loch {\f4\fs22\b1\i0\cf6 Special Note: }{\f3\fs22\b0\i0 <$Scr_Cs::5>As the scene goes along, it\loch\af3\hich\af3\dbch\af3\uc1\u8217\'92s essential to understand that Evan is still writing the confidence that the Universe had connected Maggie and him. As Maggie tells Evan all the reasons she thinks the relationship can\u8217\'92t work, throughout the scene, Evan perceives this as even more evidence that this was meant to be. He\u8217\'92s conscious of Liz\u8217\'92s \u8220\'93Love, Annually\u8221\'94 rules that warn him not to get too close to her inner circle, that the woman be at least 45 minutes away, etc. In Evan\u8217\'92s mind, the fact that she has limited free time per week and lives an hour away suits his plan perfectly. They can enjoy each other\u8217\'92s company without getting too close, and Evan\u8217\'92s mind one year is up; it\u8217\'92ll be more like friends going their own way than soulmates breaking up.<!$Scr_Cs::5>}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\li346\fi14\sb60\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f4\fs22\b1\i0\cf7 - Maggie:}{\f3\fs22\b0\i0\cf1 <$Scr_Cs::5> While Maggie finally admits that she likes the idea of being in a relationship with Evan, she provides reason after reason why she doesn't think it'll work. As Evan knocks down each of the concerns one at a time, her resolve weekends until she finally agrees. At the beginning of the scene, Maggie's almost resigned to her belief that this will be a fun night with Evan and go no further. However, as Evan easily overcomes her concerns, she gets more optimistic as the conversation flows along. Ultimately her and Evan's enthusiasm converge near the end of the scene as they agree to start a relationship. However, she feels great compassion for Evan when she innocently asks a question about Sarah. The scene ends with her expressing her compassion with a warm gentle hug, consoling Evan.<!$Scr_Cs::5>}
\par\plain {\f4\fs22\b1\i0\cf7 - Laura:}{\f3\fs22\b0\i0\cf1 <$Scr_Cs::5> Laura makes a brief appearance at the beginning of the scene. She is excited for Maggie and Evan for their first date. She agrees to return at the end of the night to pick up Maggie, and is looking forward to hearing all the details. In a bit of a humorous exit, she passes off Maggie like a baton to Evan before heading home.<!$Scr_Cs::5><!$Scr_Ps::3>}
